Results of Operations and Financial Condition.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:8px;padding-top:6px;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">On </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">January&#160;30, 2019</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, McDonald&#8217;s Corporation (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) issued an investor release reporting the Company&#8217;s results for the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">fourth</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;quarter and year ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">December&#160;31, 2018</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. A copy of the related investor release is being filed as Exhibit </font><a style="text-decoration:underline;color:#0000FF;-sec-extract:exhibit;" href="exhibit991-12312018.htm"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">99.1</font></a><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;to this Form 8-K and is incorporated by reference in its entirety. Also filed herewith and incorporated by reference as Exhibit </font><a style="text-decoration:underline;color:#0000FF;-sec-extract:exhibit;" href="exhibit992-12312018.htm"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">99.2</font></a><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;is supplemental information for the quarter and year ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">December&#160;31, 2018</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. QUARTER AND FULL YEAR 2018 RESULTS AND QUARTERLY CASH DIVIDEND</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:12px;text-align:left;text-indent:48px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#8220;Our performance in 2018 was strong, driven by the Velocity Growth Plan with broad-based momentum across each of our global segments.&#160;We continued to transform our business by making substantial progress on modernising our restaurants and offering more convenience, choice and value to our customers,&#8221; said McDonald's President and Chief Executive Officer Steve Easterbrook.&#160;&#8220;We&#8217;ve now achieved 14 consecutive quarters of positive global comparable sales and our customers rewarded us with more visits in 2018, helping us to achieve two consecutive years of global guest count growth for the first time since 2012." &#160;  </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Fourth quarter</font><font Excluding these charges, consolidated operating income was flat (increased 3% in constant currencies).</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:4px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:66px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:42px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Diluted earnings per share was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$1.82</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, reflecting non-cash impairment charges of $0.18 per share, partly offset by an income tax benefit of $0.03 per share associated with the final 2018 adjustments to the provisional amounts recorded in the prior year under the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017 (&#8220;Tax Act&#8221;). Excluding these items, diluted earnings per share was $1.97, an increase of 15% (18% in constant currencies) over prior year earnings per share (excluding $0.84 per share of prior year net tax cost under the Tax Act).</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Full year highlights:</font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:66px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:42px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Global comparable sales </font><font style="font-size:10pt;">increased</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">4.5%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, reflecting positive comparable sales across all segments.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:66px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:42px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Due to the impact of the Company's strategic refranchising initiative, consolidated revenues </font><font style="font-size:10pt;">decreased</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">8%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;(8% in constant currencies).</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:66px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:42px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Consolidated operating income </font><font style="font-size:10pt;">decreased</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">8%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;(</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">8%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;in constant currencies). 2018 results included non-cash impairment and strategic restructuring charges. 2017 results reflected a gain on the sale of the Company's businesses in China and Hong Kong, partly offset by restructuring and impairment charges. Excluding these items in both years, consolidated operating income increased 2% (2% in constant currencies).</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:66px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:42px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Diluted earnings per share of </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$7.54</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-size:10pt;">increased</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">18%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;(</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">18%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;in constant currencies).  Refer to the Key Highlights - Consolidated page for additional details.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:66px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:42px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Cash provided by operations was $7.0 billion and free cash flow was $4.2 billion, a 14% increase over the prior year.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:66px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:42px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Company returned $8.5 billion to shareholders through share repurchases and dividends. In addition, the Company announced a 15% increase in its quarterly dividend to $1.16 per share beginning in the fourth quarter 2018, and increased the cash return to shareholder target for the 3-year period ending 2019 to about $25 billion.</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-indent:48px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">On January 24, 2019, McDonald's Board of Directors declared a quarterly cash dividend of $1.16 per share of common stock payable on March 15, 2019 to shareholders of record at the close of business on March 1, 2019.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;In the U.S., </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">fourth</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;quarter comparable sales increased </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">2.3%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, driven by growth in average check resulting from both product mix shifts and menu price increases. Operating income for the quarter decreased </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">1.0%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, reflecting lower Company-operated margin dollars and lower gains on sales of restaurant businesses, partly offset by higher franchised margin dollars and G&amp;A savings.</font></div><div><br></div><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">1</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><div><br></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;In the International Lead segment, fourth quarter comparable sales increased </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">5.2%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, reflecting positive results across all markets, primarily driven by the U.K., Germany and Australia. The segment's operating income increased 8% (</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">12%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;in constant currencies), due to sales-driven improvements in franchised margin dollars and higher gains on sales of restaurant businesses in the U.K. and Australia.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;In the High Growth segment, </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">fourth</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;quarter comparable sales increased </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">4.8%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, led by continued strong performance in Italy and the Netherlands, and positive results across most of the segment. The segment's operating income decreased 44% (41% in constant currencies), reflecting non-cash impairment charges. Excluding these charges, the segment's operating income decreased 2% (increased 2% in constant currencies).</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;In the Foundational markets, </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">fourth</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;quarter comparable sales increased </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">7.1%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, reflecting positive sales performance in Japan and across all geographic regions. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;Steve Easterbrook concluded, &#8220;As we begin 2019, we have confidence in our plan and the continued growth opportunities from delivery, Experience of the Future and digital.&#160;We remain committed to running great restaurants, which will continue to make a difference for our customers and drive long-term sustainable growth.&#8221;</font></div><div for the quarter and year reflected a lower effective tax rate, and stronger operating performance due to an increase in sales-driven franchised margin dollars, partly offset by the comparison to a prior year tax benefit in Japan in the fourth quarter 2017 and by lower Company-operated margin dollars due to the impact of refranchising.</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font year.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div currencies).</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div><br></div><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">3</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><div><br></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:8px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">THE FOLLOWING DEFINITIONS APPLY TO THESE TERMS AS USED THROUGHOUT THIS RELEASE </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Comparable sales represent sales at all restaurants and comparable guest counts represent the number of transactions at all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees, in operation at least thirteen months including those temporarily closed. Some of the reasons restaurants may be temporarily closed include reimaging or remodeling, rebuilding, road construction and natural disasters. Comparable sales exclude the impact of currency translation and sales from hyper-inflationary markets (currently only Venezuela).&#160;Management generally identifies hyper-inflationary markets as those markets whose cumulative inflation rate over a three-year period exceeds 100%. Management believes that these exclusions more accurately reflect the underlying business trends. Comparable sales are driven by changes in guest counts and average check, which is affected by changes in pricing and product mix. Typically, pricing has a greater impact on average check than product mix. Management reviews the increase or decrease in comparable sales and comparable guest counts compared with the same period in the prior year to assess business trends. </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Systemwide sales include sales at all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees. </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">While franchised sales are not recorded as revenues by the Company, management believes the information is important in understanding the Company's financial performance, because these sales are the basis on which the Company calculates and records franchised revenues and are indicative of the financial health of the franchisee base.</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Information in constant currency is calculated by translating current year results at prior year average exchange rates. Management reviews and analyzes business results excluding the effect of foreign currency translation, impairment and other strategic charges and gains, as well as adjustments to the provisional amounts recorded in December 2017 under the Tax Act, and bases incentive compensation plans on these results, because the Company believes this better represents underlying business trends.  </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Free cash flow is defined as cash provided by operations less capital expenditures. Management reviews this measure in order to evaluate the Company&#8217;s ability to convert net profits into cash resources, after reinvesting in the core business, that can be used to pursue opportunities to enhance shareholder value.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:8px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">RELATED COMMUNICATIONS </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">This press release should be read in conjunction with Exhibit </font><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="exhibit992-12312018.htm"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">99.2</font></a><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;in the Company's Form 8-K filing for supplemental information related to the Company's results for the quarter and year ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">December&#160;31, 2018</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">McDonald&#8217;s Corporation will broadcast its investor earnings conference call live over the Internet at 10:00 a.m. (Central Time) on </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">January&#160;30, 2019</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. A link to the live webcast will be available at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;color:#0563c1;text-decoration:underline;">www.investor.mcdonalds.com</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. There will also be an archived webcast available for a limited time thereafter.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:8px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">UPCOMING COMMUNICATIONS </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">For important news and information regarding McDonald's, including the timing of future investor conferences and earnings calls, visit the Investor Relations section of the Company's Internet home page at </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;color:#0563c1;text-decoration:underline;">www.investor.mcdonalds.com</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. McDonald's uses this website as a primary channel for disclosing key information to its investors, some of which may contain material and previously non-public information.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">ABOUT McDONALD&#8217;S</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">McDonald&#8217;s is the world&#8217;s leading global foodservice retailer with over 37,000 locations in over 100 countries. Approximately 93% of McDonald&#8217;s restaurants worldwide are owned and operated by independent local business men and women.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:8px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">This release contains certain forward-looking statements, which reflect management's expectations regarding future events and operating performance and speak only as of the date hereof. These forward-looking statements involve a number of risks and uncertainties. The factors that could cause actual results to differ materially from our expectations are detailed in the Company&#8217;s filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission, including the risk factors discussed in Exhibit </font><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="exhibit992-12312018.htm"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">99.2</font></a><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;in the Company&#8217;s Form 8-K filing on </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">January&#160;30, 2019</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. style="vertical-align:bottom;padding-left:2px;padding-top:2px;padding-bottom:2px;padding-right:2px;"><div style="text-align:right;font-size:10pt;"><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">SUPPLEMENTAL INFORMATION</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The purpose of this exhibit is to provide additional information related to the results of McDonald's Corporation (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) for the quarter and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">year</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">December&#160;31, 2018</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. This exhibit should be read in conjunction with Exhibit </font><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="exhibit991-12312018.htm"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">99.1</font></a><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Management reviews and analyzes business results excluding the effect of foreign currency translation, impairment and other strategic charges and gains, as well as adjustments to the provisional amounts recorded in December 2017 under the Tax Cuts</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">and Jobs Act of 2017 ("Tax Act"), and bases incentive compensation plans on these results, because the Company believes this better represents underlying business trends.  </font></div><div><a name="s417F8D9634535CC893EDDBA17DAC597B"></a></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Impact of Foreign Currency Translation </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">While changes in foreign currency exchange rates affect reported results, McDonald's mitigates exposures, where practical, by purchasing goods and services in local currencies, financing in local currencies and hedging certain foreign-denominated cash flows. Results excluding the effect of foreign currency translation (also referred to as constant currency) are calculated by translating current year results at prior year average exchange rates. The year reflected a positive foreign currency impact of $0.04, primarily due to the stronger Euro and British Pound during the first half of the year.</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;</font></div><div><a name="s5977749AFA485B34B84E79C4C9D9E464"></a></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Net Income and Diluted Earnings per Share </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Results for the quarter and year reflected a lower effective tax rate, and stronger operating performance due to an increase in sales-driven franchised margin dollars, partly offset by the comparison to a prior year tax benefit in Japan in the fourth quarter 2017 and by lower Company-operated margin dollars due to the impact of refranchising.</font></div><div style="line-height:174%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Outlined below is additional information for the quarter and full year:</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:underline;">Fourth Quarter:</font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; Included in the quarter results were:</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:72px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:48px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#9702;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">approximately $140 million, or $0.18 per share, of non-cash impairment charges; and</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:72px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:48px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#9702;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">approximately $25 million, or $0.03 per share, of income tax benefit associated with final 2018 adjustments to the provisional amounts recorded in the prior year under the Tax Act.</font></div></td></tr></table><div><br></div><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">1</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><div><br></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:24px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Full year diluted earnings per share of $7.54 increased 18% (18% in constant currencies). Included in the full year results were:</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:72px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:48px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#9702;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">approximately $140 million, or $0.17 per share, of non-cash impairment charges;</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; and</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:72px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:48px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#9702;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">approximately $75 million, or $0.10 per share, of net tax cost associated with 2018 adjustments to the provisional amounts recorded in the prior year under the Tax Act.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:24px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Excluding the above items, as well as the prior year provisional net tax cost of approximately $700 million under the Tax Act, a pre-tax gain of approximately $850 million on the sale of the Company&#8217;s businesses in China and Hong Kong, and $150 million of restructuring and impairment charges, for a total net cost of $0.29 per share, full year net income was $6,205.3 million, an increase of 14% (14% in constant currencies), and diluted earnings per share was $7.90, an increase of 19% (18% in constant currencies).</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Diluted earnings per share for both periods benefited from a decrease in diluted weighted average shares outstanding due to share repurchases. During the quarter, the Company repurchased </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">5.5 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;shares of stock for </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$966.6 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, bringing total purchases for the year to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">32.2 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;shares or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$5.2 billion</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">.  In addition, the Company paid a quarterly dividend of </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$1.16</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;per share, or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$892.5 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, bringing total dividends paid for the year to </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$3.3 billion</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">.  </font></div><div><a name="s849F194E3833587EA91B53B9DB748AA2"></a></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Revenues </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Revenues consist of sales by Company-operated restaurants and fees from restaurants operated by franchisees. Revenues from conventional franchised restaurants include rent and royalties based on a percent of sales with minimum rent payments, and initial fees. Revenues from franchised restaurants that are licensed to affiliates and developmental licensees include a royalty based on a percent of sales and generally include initial fees. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Company has continually reviewed its mix of Company-owned and franchised restaurants to help optimize overall performance, with a goal to be approximately 95% franchised over the long term. Franchised restaurants represent approximately 93% of McDonald's restaurants worldwide at December 31, 2018. Although refranchising allows the Company to generate more stable and predictable revenue and cash flow streams while operating with a less resource-intensive structure, the shift to a greater percentage of franchised restaurants negatively impacts consolidated revenues as Company-operated sales are replaced by franchised revenues, where the Company receives rent and/or royalty revenue based on a percentage of sales.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Effective January 1, 2018, the Company adopted the guidance issued in Accounting Standards Codification 606, "Revenue Recognition - Revenue from Contracts with Customers." This standard changed the way initial fees from franchisees for new restaurant openings and new franchise terms are recognized. Under the new guidance, initial franchise fees are being recognized evenly over the franchise term rather than immediately upon receipt. Revenues for the quarter and year reflected a negative impact of approximately $17 million and $42 million, respectively, due to the timing of new restaurant openings and new franchise terms. style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">International Lead Markets:</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Revenues decreased for the quarter and increased for the year. In constant currencies, revenues increased for both periods as positive comparable sales across all markets were partly offset by the impact of refranchising. </font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:60px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:30px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">High Growth Markets:</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Revenues decreased for both periods. In constant currencies, revenues increased for the quarter reflecting positive comparable sales across most markets and decreased for the year reflecting positive comparable sales across most markets that were more than offset by the impact of refranchising the Company's businesses in China and Hong Kong in the third quarter 2017.</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div><a name="sA870B2C2706155C8B04665DF8A44DA7F"></a></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Comparable Sales and Guest Counts</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Comparable sales is a key performance indicator used within the retail industry and is reviewed by management to assess business trends. Comparable sales exclude the impact of currency translation and sales from hyper-inflationary markets (currently only Venezuela). Increases or decreases in comparable sales represent the percent change in constant currency sales from the same period in the prior year for all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees, in operation at least thirteen months, including those temporarily closed. Comparable sales are driven by changes in guest counts and average check, which is affected by changes in pricing and product mix. Typically, pricing has a greater impact on average check than product mix. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:12px;text-align:left;padding-left:0px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">COMPARABLE SALES AND GUEST COUNTS </font><div style="padding-left:0px;text-indent:0px;line-height:normal;padding-top:10px;"><table cellpadding="0" style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Operating Income: </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Operating income </font><font style="font-size:10pt;">decreased</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$144.7 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">7%</font><font the quarter and </font><font style="font-size:10pt;">decreased</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">$730.1 million</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;or </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">8%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;(</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">8%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;in constant currencies) for the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">year</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">. Results for the quarter and year 2018 included approximately $140 million of non-cash impairment charges. Results for the year 2018 also included strategic restructuring charges of $94 million (of which $85 million relates to the restructuring of the U.S. business). The results for the year 2017 included a gain of approximately $850 million on the sale of the Company's businesses in China and Hong Kong, partly offset by $150 million of restructuring and impairment charges. Excluding these current year and prior year items, operating income decreased $6.9 million for the quarter, a flat percentage change to prior year (increased 3% in constant currencies) and increased $204.3 million or 2% (2% in constant currencies) for the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">year</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:60px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:30px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">U.S.: </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Results for both periods reflected higher franchised margin dollars and lower G&amp;A costs, offset by lower Company-operated margin dollars. Results for the year also reflected the $85 million strategic restructuring charge. Excluding this charge, operating income for the year increased 2%. </font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:60px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:30px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">International Lead Markets: </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The constant currency operating income increase for the quarter and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">year</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;was primarily due to sales-driven improvements in franchised margin dollars across all markets and higher gains on sales of restaurant businesses in the U.K. and Australia. Results for the year also reflected the comparison to a prior year gain on the strategic sale of property in Australia.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:60px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:30px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">High Growth Markets:</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Excluding the current quarter impairment charges, operating income for the quarter decreased 2% (increased 2% in constant currencies). The constant currency increase for the quarter reflected higher franchised margin dollars due to higher sales-driven performance across most markets. Excluding the 2018 and 2017 impairment charges and the 2017 gain on the sale of the Company's businesses in China and Hong Kong, operating income decreased 10% (11% in constant currencies) for the year due to the impact of refranchising in China and Hong Kong.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:60px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:30px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Foundational Markets &amp; Corporate:</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;The constant currency operating income decrease for both periods primarily reflected higher G&amp;A costs in Corporate, mainly due to investments in restaurant technology, as well as the comparison to a prior year tax benefit in Japan in the fourth quarter 2017.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:12px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:24px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Operating Margin:</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Operating margin is defined as operating income as a percent of total revenues. Operating margin was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">42.0%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">41.9%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;for the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">year</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">s </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">2018</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">2017</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, respectively. Excluding the previously described 2018 impairment and strategic restructuring charges and the 2017 gain, and restructuring and impairment charges, operating margin was 43.1% and 38.8% for the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">year</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">s 2018 and 2017, respectively.  </font></div></td></tr></table><div><br></div><div style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></td></tr></table></div></div><div><a name="s260D0A6699815985B89F883A04FE9D29"></a></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Income Taxes</font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:30px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The effective income tax rate was </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">19.2%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">62.9%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;for the quarters ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">2018</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">2017</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, respectively, and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">24.2%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">39.4%</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;for the </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">years</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;ended </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">2018</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;and </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">2017</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">, respectively.  The effective income tax rate for the quarter and year 2018 reflected the final 2018 adjustments to the provisional amounts recorded in the prior year under the Tax Act of approximately $25 million tax benefit for the quarter and approximately $75 million net tax cost for the year.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:30px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Excluding the impact of the Tax Act and the current year impairment charges, the effective income tax rate was 19.2% for the quarter 2018 and 22.9% for the year 2018. </font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:30px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Excluding the prior year provisional net tax cost of approximately $700 million under the Tax Act, the effective income tax rate was 27.4% for the quarter 2017 and 31.6% for the year 2017.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:6px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:30px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Excluding the impact of the Tax Act and the current year impairment charges, the lower effective income tax rate for the quarter and year 2018 reflected the reduction in the U.S. corporate tax rate from 35% to 21% in 2018. In addition, both the fourth quarter 2018 and 2017 reflected a benefit from a change in tax reserves as a result of global audit progression.</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div><a name="sD9A91C6F87C255AAADA05416D4747216"></a></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:12px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Cash Flows</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Company generates significant cash from its operations and has substantial credit availability and capacity to fund operating and discretionary spending such as capital expenditures, debt repayments, dividends and share repurchases.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Cash provided by operations totaled $7.0 billion and free cash flow was $4.2 billion in 2018, an increase in free cash flow of $528 million or 14% compared with 2017. Cash provided by operations totaled $5.6 billion and free cash flow was $3.7 billion in 2017.  In 2018, cash provided by operations increased by $1.4 billion or 25% compared with 2017, primarily due to lower tax payments.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Cash used for investing activities totaled $2.5 billion in 2018, an increase of $3 billion compared with 2017. The increase is primarily due to lower proceeds from the sale of restaurant businesses in 2018, as well as higher capital expenditures. Cash provided by investing activities totaled $562 million in 2017. 2017 reflected proceeds associated with the sale of the Company's businesses in China and Hong Kong, as well as the sale of its businesses in Denmark, Finland, Norway and Sweden (referred to as the &#8220;Nordics&#8221;) and Taiwan to developmental licensees.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Cash used for financing activities totaled $5.9 billion in 2018, an increase of $639 million compared with 2017, primarily due to higher treasury stock purchases. Cash used for financing activities totaled $5.3 billion in 2017.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:6px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div><br></div><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">9</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div><a name="sFB921600AA7A52E7994764338D205658"></a></div><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><div><br></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">2019 Outlook</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;text-indent:30px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The following information is provided to assist in forecasting the Company&#8217;s future results.</font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Changes in Systemwide sales are driven by comparable sales, net restaurant unit expansion, and the potential impacts of hyper-inflation. The Company expects net restaurant additions to add approximately 1 percentage point to 2019 Systemwide sales growth (in constant currencies).</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Company does not generally provide specific guidance on changes in comparable sales. However, as a perspective, assuming no change in cost structure, a 1 percentage point change in comparable sales for either the U.S. or the new International Operated Markets segment would change annual diluted earnings per share by about 6 to 7 cents. </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">With about 75% of McDonald's grocery bill comprised of 10 different commodities, a basket of goods approach is the most comprehensive way to look at the Company's commodity costs. For the full year 2019, costs for the total basket of goods are expected to increase about 1% to 2% in the U.S. and about 2% in key markets outside of the U.S.*</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Company expects full year 2019 selling, general and administrative expenses to decrease about 4% in constant currencies. This decrease will result in expected G&amp;A of approximately $2.1 billion at current exchange rates for full year 2019, reflecting completion of about $500 million of net savings from our G&amp;A budget of $2.6 billion at the beginning of 2015. </font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Based on current interest and foreign currency exchange rates, the Company expects interest expense for the full year 2019 to increase about 10% to 12% due primarily to higher average debt balances.</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">A significant part of the Company's operating income is generated outside the U.S., and about 40% of its total debt is denominated in foreign currencies. Accordingly, earnings are affected by changes in foreign currency exchange rates, particularly the Euro, British Pound, Australian Dollar and Canadian Dollar. Collectively, these currencies represent approximately 80% of the Company's operating income outside the U.S. If all four of these currencies moved by 10% in the same direction, the Company's annual diluted earnings per share would change by about 35 cents.</font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Company expects the effective income tax rate for the full year 2019 to be in the 24% to 26% range. Some volatility may result in a quarterly tax rate outside of the annual range.</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">The Company expects capital expenditures for 2019 to be approximately $2.3 billion. About $1.5 billion will be dedicated to our U.S. business, nearly two-thirds of which is allocated to approximately 2,000 EOTF projects. Globally, we expect to open roughly 1,200 restaurants. We will spend approximately $600 million in our wholly owned markets to open 300 restaurants and our developmental licensee and affiliated markets will contribute capital towards the remaining 900 restaurant openings in their respective markets. The Company expects about 750 net restaurant additions in 2019. </font><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:64px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:38px;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">&#8226;</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">During 2019, the Company expects to return about $9 billion to shareholders, which will complete its cash return to shareholder target of about $25 billion for the 3-year period ending 2019.</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div (constant currency) financial targets:</font></div></td></tr></table><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="padding-top:5px;font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td range.</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-top:5px;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div and the U.K.</font></div><div><br></div><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">10</font></div></div><hr
